Dorothy Hawkes GALT, Appellant, v. Harriet Virginia GALT, Appellee. No. 8377. United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia. Argued Oct 12, 1943. Decided Oct. 25, 1943. Mr. J. Edward Bindeman, of Washington, D. C., for appellant. Mr. F. Regis Noel, of Washington, D. C., for appellee.

Before GRONER, Chief Justice, and ED-GERTON and ARNOLD, Associate Justices.

PER CURIAM.

A careful examination of the record discloses no reversible error, and the order is, therefore,

Affirmed.
